<title>UK: ALLIED DOMECQ FIRM ON NATWEST TRADE UPDATE.</title>
<headline>ALLIED DOMECQ FIRM ON NATWEST TRADE UPDATE.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in drinks group Allied Domecq Plc crept higher on Wednesday, supported by a trade update from NatWest securities following a meeting with the company.</p>
<p>    The shares were up 2-1/2p to 477p by 0900 GMT.    After the pre-closed season meeting, NatWest retained its hold stance on the stock but said the outlook for the company was upbeat with the international spirits division going better, market sources said.</p>
<p>-- Elaine Hardcastle, London Newsroom +44 171 542 4027</p>
